item.title: Fireworks in Venice , the Feast of the Redeemer, By Vincenzo Abbati (Italian,1803 – 1866)
item.description: Fireworks in Venice, the Feast of the Redeemer By Vincenzo Abbati (Italian, 1803 – 1866) Overview: “Fireworks in Venice, the Feast of the Redeemer” is a painting by the Italian artist Vincenzo Abbati. The painting captures the vibrant and festive atmosphere of one of Venice’s most significant annual events, the Festa del Redentore (Feast of the Redeemer). About the Artist: Name: Vincenzo Abbati Born: 1803 Died: 1866 Nationality: Italian Known For: Abbati was renowned for his skill in depicting architectural interiors and cityscapes.
